    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Mentioned by <bibl><ptr target="#cdl1987a"/>, pp. <citedRange>88-89</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>37.1734</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>080300</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#zimmermann1996"/>, p. 141, n. <citedRange>577</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>46.2330</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>ιμ<unclear>ω</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Λεβύστρατος"><seg part="I"><supplied reason="lost">Λ</supplied>εβυσ<supplied reason="lost">τρατ</supplied></seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name><gap reason="lost" quantity="2" unit="character"/><seg part="M">ριο</seg><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName>
                    <lb n="3a"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <rdg resp="#cdl1987a"><supplied reason="lost">Λ</supplied>έβυς</rdg>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="3"><note>This line omitted in <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/></bibl></note></app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Lebystrat<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>rio<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Lebystrat<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>rio<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> Lebystrat<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>, <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>rio<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>We suspect the first line to contain a personal name. With a tau restituted before the preserved segment, we might have either the end of a name in -<foreign xml:lang="grc">τιμος</foreign> or
                    the beginning of <foreign xml:lang="grc">Τιμῶναξ</foreign>. The piece is too lacunar to allow a choice.</p>
                <p>For the name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Λεβύστρατος/Λιβύστρατος</foreign>, see <bibl><ptr target="#masson1975a"/>, pp. <citedRange>712-713</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
	           <p>At line 3, if we also have a personal name, the poor vestiges escape restoration.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
